Scope Creep Escalation.body:
// Step 1 — Initial Redirect
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I've noted the new feature requests. As a reminder, the scope was locked on [DATE] and these items fall outside it. I've attached the signed scope document for reference. I can quote these separately if you'd like to proceed after the current build is complete.

// Step 2 — Firm Boundary
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand you'd like these additions. However, continuing to add requests outside the locked scope will delay the project and increase costs. I need to complete the agreed work first. Once that's delivered, I'm happy to discuss a phase two engagement.

// Step 3 — Final Position
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I need to be direct. The current scope cannot absorb additional features without a new agreement. I will complete the original deliverables by [DATE] as agreed. Any further additions require a separate signed scope and deposit. This is how I protect both your timeline and my capacity. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}, {{BUSINESS_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Reminder
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, we've now completed [NUMBER] revision rounds. Your package includes [INCLUDED NUMBER]. I'm happy to continue refining, but additional rounds are billed at [RATE] per round. Let me know how you'd like to proceed.

// Step 2 — Boundary Hold
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I've received another round of changes. As mentioned, we've exceeded the included revisions. I'll need payment of [AMOUNT] before I can begin this round. I want to make sure we're aligned before I continue work.

// Step 3 — Clear Escalation
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand you want the design to be right. Going forward, each revision round requires prepayment. I will not begin additional work without a confirmed payment. This ensures the project stays manageable for both of us. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}, {{BUSINESS_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Clarification
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, the training you're requesting wasn't included in the project scope. I delivered the system as agreed, with documentation. Training sessions are available at [RATE] per hour. I can schedule one if you'd like.

// Step 2 — Hold the Line
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand you'd like more support. The documentation I provided covers the core functions. If you need hands-on training, that's a separate engagement. I need your confirmation and payment before scheduling any training sessions.

// Step 1 — Redirect
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, the additional rooms you've mentioned aren't covered in our current agreement. I can add them, but it will require a scope amendment with revised pricing and timeline. I'll send that through for your review.

// Step 2 — Firm Restatement
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I've received another request to include [ROOM] in the current project. As I mentioned, this requires a formal scope amendment. I'm not able to absorb additional rooms into the existing budget. Please review the amendment I sent on [DATE] and let me know your decision.

// Step 3 — Deadline for Decision
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I need a decision on the scope amendment by [DATE] so I can plan my schedule accordingly. If I don't hear back, I'll proceed with the original scope only. Either way, I'm committed to delivering excellent work on what's been agreed. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}, {{BUSINESS_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Initial Boundary
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, nutrition planning isn't included in your training package. Your plan covers [INCLUDED SERVICES]. I offer nutrition coaching as a separate add-on at [RATE/MONTH]. Let me know if you'd like me to send the details.

// Step 2 — Repeated Request
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand nutrition feels connected to your goals. However, it's a separate service that requires dedicated time and expertise. I'm not able to include it in your current training sessions. If you'd like to add it, I'll send the proposal today.

// Step 1 — Clarification
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, your package includes [NUMBER] edited digital images. Raw/unedited files are not included in this package. If you'd like to purchase the raw files, they're available for an additional [AMOUNT]. Let me know if you'd like to add that.

// Step 2 — Firm Hold
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand you'd prefer to have the raws. My policy on this is consistent across all clients. Raw files are a separate purchase. The edited images you've received are the final deliverables under our agreement. Let me know if you'd like to purchase the raws separately.

// Step 3 — Final Statement
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I've explained the raw file policy twice now. The edited images are your deliverables. Raws are available at the price I quoted. I won't be releasing them without that purchase. This is a standard practice and it's non-negotiable. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}, {{BUSINESS_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Scope Reminder
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, the questions you're raising fall into business advisory rather than standard accounting. Your engagement covers [TAX/BAS/BOOKKEEPING]. Advisory services are available at [RATE/HOUR]. I can schedule an advisory session if you'd like.

// Step 2 — Enforcing the Boundary
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I've noticed several recent requests that fall under advisory work. I want to help, but I need to charge appropriately for the time and expertise involved. Going forward, advisory questions will be handled in paid sessions only. Let me know if you'd like to book one.

// Step 1 — Flag the Expansion
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, the campaign deliverables have expanded beyond what was scoped. The original agreement covers [ORIGINAL SCOPE]. The additions you've requested represent approximately [HOURS/AMOUNT] in additional work. I'll send a change order for your approval.

// Step 2 — Hold Pending Approval
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I've sent the change order on [DATE] and haven't received approval yet. I'm unable to begin the additional work until it's signed and the deposit is received. The original campaign deliverables remain on schedule.

// Step 3 — Final Position
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I need the change order resolved. If approved, I'll begin the additional work immediately. If not, I'll deliver the original scope as agreed and we can revisit the additions in a future campaign. I need your decision by [DATE]. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}, {{BUSINESS_NAME}}

Pricing Pushback.body:
// Step 1 — Clear Decline
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I appreciate the volume of work. My pricing at {{BUSINESS_NAME}} is per-session and already reflects a competitive rate for the quality delivered. I don't offer bulk discounts. The quoted rate of [AMOUNT] per session is my standard and applies to all clients.

// Step 2 — Final Position
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand you'd like a different arrangement. My rate is firm. If budget is a constraint, I can suggest a smaller package that fits your budget while still delivering professional results. Otherwise, I'd need you to confirm the original quote to proceed. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Acknowledge Without Budging
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand your previous provider had different pricing. My rates at {{BUSINESS_NAME}} are based on my experience, deliverable quality, and the support included. I'm confident in the value I provide at [AMOUNT]. I'm not in a position to adjust based on another provider's pricing.

// Step 2 — Close the Loop
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I've given this thought and my pricing stands as quoted. If you'd like to explore a reduced scope to fit your budget, I can offer options. Otherwise, I'd need a decision by [DATE] so I can manage my schedule. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Respectful Decline
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I appreciate the offer, but {{BUSINESS_NAME}} operates on paid engagements only. Exposure doesn't cover the time, tools, and expertise that go into the work. I'd be happy to work with you on a paid basis. Here's what I can offer within [BUDGET RANGE].

// Step 2 — Final Word
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, my position on this hasn't changed. All work at {{BUSINESS_NAME}} is paid work. If your budget allows for a paid engagement in the future, I'd welcome the conversation. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Decline
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, my payment terms at {{BUSINESS_NAME}} require [DEPOSIT PERCENTAGE] upfront before work begins. This is standard across all projects and protects both parties. I'm not able to begin work on a post-delivery payment basis. Once the deposit is received, I'll schedule your start date.

// Step 2 — Hold Firm
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand that's not your preference. My terms are non-negotiable on this point. The deposit ensures I can allocate time and resources to your project. If you'd like to proceed, please arrange the deposit of [AMOUNT] by [DATE]. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}

// Step 1 — Set the Boundary
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I understand it seems like a small request. Even small tasks require my time and expertise, and I price my services accordingly. I'm not able to do this one for free. I can add it to your next session, or I can quote it as a standalone. Let me know what works.

// Step 2 — Reinforce
{{CLIENT_NAME}}, I appreciate your understanding. My approach at {{BUSINESS_NAME}} is to charge fairly for all work, regardless of size. If you'd like to add this to a paid session, I'm happy to accommodate. Otherwise, I'll focus on your current plan as agreed. - {{YOUR_FIRST_NAME}}
